'''''Hafrada''''' ('''הפרדה''') is a [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] word that means "separation". The term has been used to describe a policy of the [[Israel]]i government to create a border which seperates the [[Palestinian territories]] occupied by Israel from the Israeli population center, by means of the [[Israeli West Bank barrier]] and unilateral disengagement from those territories. 

